      "answer": "Potassium is the priority during heat/stress to regulate water use. Use potash (K2SO4) or potassium-rich compost extracts, avoiding calcium-heavy amendments unless lime deficiency exists first.",
      "rubric": "- Correctly identifies Potassium as the primary need.\n- Selects a safe K-salt source like K2SO4 over Chlorides.\n- Avoids suggesting Calcium-based fixes without context of leaf margins.",
