      "answer": "Mix in aged manure or biochar. These improve water holding capacity and cation exchange capacity (CEC). Mix consistently at least 4-6 inches deep to ensure root zone stability.",
      "rubric": "- Selects a long-term structural amendment like manure/biochar.\n- Specifies mixing depth of ~5+ inches.\n- Focuses on structure/water retention rather than NPK balance only.",
      "skill": "apply"
    }
